Amazing! 8 year old Angelina Jordan, winner of Norway\`s Got Talent 2014, performs Dinah Washingtons "What a Difference a Day Made" on the opening show of TV 2 singalong summer hit "Allsang på grensen" on Thursday June 3rd 2014. The song was written in Spanish by María Grever, a Mexican songwriter, in 1934. Originally, the song was known as "Cuando vuelva a tu lado" ("When I Return to Your Side"). The song is also known in English as "What a Diff'rence a Day Makes", as popularized by Dinah Washington. The English lyrics were written by Stanley Adams, and was played by Harry Roy & his Orchestra. It was published in late 1934. The most successful early recording, in 1934, was by the Dorsey Brothers. See This 8-Year-Old Norwegian Girl Sing Frank Sinatra Perfectly
===============================================================
Norway's Angelina Jordan sang "Fly Me to the Moon" on late-night show _Senkveld_
By 
Published on May 7, 2014 11:15AM EDT
!:max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(299x0:301x2):format(webp)/angelina-jordan-600x4501-267d3215f0cf4a60b5b0e6b455d02e1a.jpg)
Photo: Movie Clips
Despite being born years after , Norway’s Angelina Jordan has done ‘s memory proud.
On a March appearance on Norwegian late-night show _Senkveld_, the 7-year-old  sang Sinatra’s classic  in a jazzy style that belied her young age. (She has since turned 8.)
Maybe it’s her accent, but something about Jordan’s singing is able to transport us back to the smoky bars of the 1950s, a time when men wore hats and women were “gals.”
Watch the video above, and then see some of Jordan’s other covers below:
